Who doesn't love Joseph Lai?  The man who brought you Ninja Terminator.

The splicing film in this episode is some almost unbearably grim thuggish gangster story, almost incomprehensible.  It looks to be Malaysian, but there are several apparently Thai locations, so you figure it out.  Just lots of hammer-fisted, torso-swinging punches in this one!  Not a lot of that fancy kung fu!

Unless you count the parts with Gordon and his ninja buddies.  These are some of the most colorful ninjas you will ever lay eyes on!  I might be wrong, but weren't ninjas supposed to be stealthy?  So what's with the red and yellow outfit???

I haven't had a chance to watch the other film included, but it looks to be good-and-grimy full-screen dubbed Kung Fu action.  Get your beer keg ready and call the gang for this feature!
